author: gstein
msg: Remove references to the now-tossed "contrib" directory on our
distribution site. Regenerated the site.
* xdocs/info/known_bugs.html: this file was *SO* out of date (and included
a reference to contrib/), that I simply killed it. I'm sure it is much
happier now.
* xdocs/info/index.xml: remove reference to known_bugs.html
* xdocs/dev/patches.xml: remove note that a person can have their patch
placed into our contrib area. sorry, but no. if we don't want it, then
we aren't going to distribute it.
* docs/dev/devnotes.html: picked up a regen for some other change
* docs/dev/patches.html, docs/info/index.html: regen'd for above changes
* docs/info/known_bugs.html: removed

author: gstein
msg: The "contrib" directory is totally unmaintained. It is also an exposure
that we don't really care to assume. Therefore, I've removed the directory
from minotaur (should still be available on archive, tho), and have
removed references to it from HEADER.html and README.html.
